WEBVTT

00:10.111 --> 00:12.046
[CROWD CHEERING
AND LAUGHING]

00:12.113 --> 00:14.348
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:19.720 --> 00:21.322
WELL, PARIS
WAS EXCITING,

00:21.389 --> 00:24.425
BUT HONG KONG
REALLY KNOWS HOW TO
CELEBRATE NEW YEAR'S.

00:24.492 --> 00:26.094
LIKE, YEAH.

00:26.160 --> 00:27.761
CHEER UP, SHAGGY.

00:27.828 --> 00:29.163
ENJOY THE PARADE.

00:29.230 --> 00:32.366
HOW CAN I
WHEN MY FAVORITE
BATHTUB PAL DUCK GUY

00:32.433 --> 00:34.135
WAS TOTALED
BY MY BATTLESHIP?

00:34.202 --> 00:36.437
LIKE, HE CAN'T EVEN
SAY "QUACK" ANYMORE.

00:36.504 --> 00:37.505
QUACK?

00:37.571 --> 00:40.208
THANKS, SCOOB, BUT
IT'S JUST NOT THE SAME.

00:40.274 --> 00:42.710
DON'T WORRY, SHAGGY.
WE'LL GET DUCK GUY FIXED.

00:42.776 --> 00:46.380
THE LING TOY COMPANY
WHERE HE WAS MADE IS
RIGHT HERE IN HONG KONG.

00:46.447 --> 00:49.217
HEAR THAT, DUCK GUY?
WE'RE IN YOUR HOMETOWN.

00:49.283 --> 00:53.354
LOOK, THERE'S EVEN
ONE OF THEIR STORES.

01:02.130 --> 01:03.397
HEY, CHECK THAT,
SCOOB--

01:03.464 --> 01:06.300
A CANDY RING
WORTH ONE MILLION BUCKS.

01:06.367 --> 01:11.472
LIKE, ANY CANDY
AGED 500 YEARS HAS
GOT TO BE PRIMO TASTY.

01:11.539 --> 01:12.506
YUMMY.

01:12.573 --> 01:15.743
JEEPERS, WHAT
A BEAUTIFUL DRAGON.

01:17.811 --> 01:19.147
[CROWD GASPS]

01:19.213 --> 01:21.449
[ROARING]

01:24.452 --> 01:25.586
ZOINKS!

01:25.653 --> 01:27.621
[CROWD YELLING]

01:29.323 --> 01:30.424
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:30.491 --> 01:32.092
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:32.160 --> 01:34.928
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:34.995 --> 01:36.197
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:36.264 --> 01:38.031
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

01:38.098 --> 01:40.968
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:41.034 --> 01:42.170
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:42.236 --> 01:43.537
* WE'RE GONNA FOLLOW YOU *

01:43.604 --> 01:46.340
* YOU'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

01:46.407 --> 01:47.575
* WE SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

01:47.641 --> 01:49.577
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

01:49.643 --> 01:53.147
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

01:54.315 --> 01:55.649
* DON'T LOOK BACK *

01:55.716 --> 01:58.786
* YOU MAY FIND
ANOTHER CLUE *

02:00.354 --> 02:04.492
* SCOOBY SNAX WILL BE
WAITING HERE FOR YOU *

02:04.558 --> 02:06.227
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

02:06.294 --> 02:07.661
* WE'RE COMING AFTER YOU *

02:07.728 --> 02:10.264
* WE'RE GONNA SOLVE
THAT MYSTERY *

02:10.331 --> 02:11.499
* I SEE YOU, SCOOBY-DOO *

02:11.565 --> 02:13.401
* THE TRAIL
LEADS BACK TO YOU *

02:13.467 --> 02:16.270
* WHAT'S NEW, SCOOBY-DOO? *

02:16.337 --> 02:17.971
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

02:18.038 --> 02:19.307
* NA-NA NA-NA NA *

02:19.373 --> 02:22.276
* NA-NA NA NA NA-NA NA *

02:22.343 --> 02:25.679
* NA-NA NA-NA NA
NA-NA NA-NA NA *

02:30.017 --> 02:31.719
[ROARING]

02:31.785 --> 02:33.554
Fred: EVERYBODY DIVE!

02:35.289 --> 02:36.824
[BOTH SCREAMING]

02:41.229 --> 02:43.497
[SCREAMING]

02:45.199 --> 02:47.501
[ROARS]

02:54.475 --> 02:57.077
Velma: JINKIES!
THE CANDY RING IS GONE.

02:57.144 --> 02:58.746
HEY!
HEY!

02:58.812 --> 02:59.980
I'M DETECTIVE KANG.

03:00.047 --> 03:01.682
DID YOU KIDS
SEE THAT DRAGON?

03:01.749 --> 03:03.784
OUR FRIEND WAS STANDING
RIGHT NEAR ITS FACE.

03:03.851 --> 03:06.787
GIVES NEW MEANING TO
THE TERM DRAGON BREATH.

03:06.854 --> 03:09.623
FINALLY, A CASE THAT
WILL STOP THEM LAUGHING

03:09.690 --> 03:12.092
AND PUT ME ON
THE CRIME-SOLVING MAP.

03:12.159 --> 03:13.561
WHO'S LAUGHING?

03:13.627 --> 03:14.628
WHO ISN'T?

03:14.695 --> 03:16.564
"CAUGHT IN
HIS OWN HANDCUFFS" KANG,

03:16.630 --> 03:18.899
"SWALLOWED
THE EVIDENCE" KANG.

03:18.966 --> 03:20.668
WELL, NOW
I'M GOING TO BE

03:20.734 --> 03:23.203
"THE DRAGON HUNTER
OF HONG KONG" KANG.

03:23.271 --> 03:25.673
OUT OF MY WAY!
I'M GOING TO CATCH A DRAGON.

03:25.739 --> 03:27.808
WELL, WE'RE GOING
TO THE LING TOY COMPANY.

03:27.875 --> 03:28.876
WE ARE?

03:28.942 --> 03:31.312
WE NOW HAVE A LIVE
MYSTERY ON OUR HANDS...

03:31.379 --> 03:34.248
AND A DEAD DUCK.

03:38.319 --> 03:39.787
FOR A MODERN CITY...

03:39.853 --> 03:42.623
HONG KONG SURE HAS
SOME EERIE STREETS.

03:42.690 --> 03:44.057
WELL, YOU'RE
SAFE WITH ME.

03:44.124 --> 03:46.059
I'M READING THIS
BOOK ON JU-JITSU.

03:46.126 --> 03:47.328
I THINK
IT'S LIKE KARATE,

03:47.395 --> 03:48.996
BUT WITH
A LOT MORE YELLING.

03:49.062 --> 03:51.164
HYAH! OOH-AAH!

03:51.231 --> 03:53.501
HYAH-YANA!

03:55.202 --> 03:56.604
YIKES!

03:56.670 --> 03:58.839
SHAGGY, YOU'RE
NOT AFRAID OF
YOUR OWN SHADOW.

03:58.906 --> 04:02.576
LIKE, THAT SHADOW
WASN'T MY SHADOW.

04:02.643 --> 04:03.877
[MOANS]

04:03.944 --> 04:04.945
AAH!
YIKES!

04:05.012 --> 04:06.280
Both: AAH!

04:07.147 --> 04:08.716
WE'RE HERE
TO SAVE DUCK GUY.

04:08.782 --> 04:09.883
WHO'S IN CHARGE?

04:09.950 --> 04:11.752
I'M THE OWNER,
HAROLD LING.

04:11.819 --> 04:13.954
HE'S MET WITH
A TUB-RELATED EMERGENCY.

04:14.021 --> 04:16.290
WILL HE PULL THROUGH?

04:16.357 --> 04:17.391
I'M AFRAID NOT.

04:17.458 --> 04:20.027
YOU MEAN DUCK GUY'S
DONE FOR?

04:20.093 --> 04:21.194
I'D LIKE TO HELP YOU,
BUT I'VE GOT

04:21.261 --> 04:23.497
SOME BIG PROBLEMS
OF MY OWN RIGHT NOW.

04:23.564 --> 04:25.933
ONE OF MY STORES
WAS BROKEN INTO.

04:25.999 --> 04:27.267
WE KNOW.
WE WERE THERE.

04:27.335 --> 04:29.870
YOU WERE? WAS
THE CANDY RING STOLEN?

04:29.937 --> 04:32.005
I'M AFRAID IT WAS.

04:32.072 --> 04:34.408
THAT WAS
MY PRIZE POSSESSION.

04:34.475 --> 04:37.177
THAT CANDY RING
BELONGED TO
THE LITTLE MING EMPEROR

04:37.244 --> 04:38.812
OVER 500 YEARS AGO.

04:38.879 --> 04:40.881
DO YOU HAVE ANY ENEMIES
WHO WOULD DO THAT?

04:40.948 --> 04:43.951
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
THE MAN WHO CREATED
THAT DUCK.

04:44.017 --> 04:45.986
HE WAS ONCE
A CHILD GENIUS--

04:46.053 --> 04:47.888
LOUIE HONG FA.

04:47.955 --> 04:50.223
BUT NOW I THINK
HE'S OUT TO GET ME.

04:50.290 --> 04:51.859
WHY WOULD HE
DO THAT?

04:51.925 --> 04:52.960
BECAUSE I FIRED HIM.

04:53.026 --> 04:54.294
BUT I HAD NO CHOICE.

04:54.362 --> 04:56.830
HE WENT LOONY, CREATING
ONLY TOYS THAT--

04:56.897 --> 04:58.932
WELL, SEE FOR YOURSELF.

05:00.000 --> 05:01.268
[CLICK]

05:01.335 --> 05:02.436
YAAH!

05:02.503 --> 05:04.505
WHOA!
YAAH!

05:04.572 --> 05:06.974
OH!

05:07.040 --> 05:08.008
ZOINKS!

05:08.075 --> 05:09.343
Fred: WOW!
THAT IS BIG.

05:09.410 --> 05:10.511
TOO BIG.

05:10.578 --> 05:12.380
THE ONLY TOYS LOUIE
MADE LATELY

05:12.446 --> 05:14.081
WERE THESE
GIANT MUTANTS.

05:14.147 --> 05:15.315
WHO WOULD WANT THAT?

05:15.383 --> 05:16.817
EVERY KID I KNOW.

05:16.884 --> 05:19.119
YEAH, AND DOG!

05:19.186 --> 05:20.454
BUT NOT ONE PARENT.

05:20.521 --> 05:23.123
CAN YOU IMAGINE WHAT
THEIR HOUSE WOULD BE LIKE?

05:23.190 --> 05:24.792
HMM...

05:26.093 --> 05:27.495
AAH!

05:31.098 --> 05:33.133
I'D BETTER GET A LADDER.

05:33.200 --> 05:35.235
"W.H. 12."

05:35.302 --> 05:36.937
I WONDER WHAT THAT MEANS?

05:37.004 --> 05:39.006
[ROARING]

05:48.416 --> 05:49.349
YIKES!

05:49.417 --> 05:51.084
Shaggy: HELP US!

06:02.362 --> 06:03.063
UNH!

06:03.130 --> 06:04.097
LIKE, THANKS!

06:04.164 --> 06:06.567
YEAH, THANKS!

06:07.501 --> 06:09.002
AAH!
AAH!

06:09.069 --> 06:10.438
UHH!

06:11.972 --> 06:14.475
LOOKS LIKE YOU GUYS
HAVE A GUARDIAN ANGEL.

06:14.542 --> 06:17.010
Shaggy: LIKE, TWO
DEMOLISHING DRAGON SIGHTINGS

06:17.077 --> 06:18.311
IS TWO TOO MANY.

06:18.378 --> 06:21.148
I'VE BEEN CURSED
BY A BAD LUCK DRAGON.

06:21.214 --> 06:22.950
MY SHOP AND RING--

06:23.016 --> 06:24.518
NOW MY COMPANY.

06:24.585 --> 06:26.286
I'VE ONLY GOT
ONE STORE LEFT.

06:26.353 --> 06:28.055
IT COULD BE IN DANGER.
WHERE IS IT?

06:28.121 --> 06:31.659
THE MALL AT VICTORIA PEAK,
UP THE 800-FOOT ESCALATOR.

06:31.725 --> 06:32.560
MALL?

06:32.626 --> 06:33.827
BUT IT'S CLOSED.

06:33.894 --> 06:35.896
NOBODY'S UP THERE
TO WATCH MY STORE.

06:35.963 --> 06:36.930
COME ON, GANG.

06:36.997 --> 06:38.799
WE'RE GOING
FOR AN ESCALATOR RIDE.

06:42.402 --> 06:45.673
Velma: WE'RE HEADED
FOR THE HIGHEST POINT
IN HONG KONG.

06:45.739 --> 06:49.409
LET US KNOW
WHEN THIS THING LANDS.

06:51.779 --> 06:54.347
COULDN'T WE COME BACK
DURING THE DAY?

06:54.414 --> 06:55.716
WHAT COULD BE CREEPIER

06:55.783 --> 06:57.551
THAN A MALL WHERE
YOU CAN'T GO SHOPPING?

06:57.618 --> 06:58.719
[MEN GRUNTING]

06:58.786 --> 07:00.420
THAT COULD BE
CREEPIER!

07:00.488 --> 07:04.224
RACE YOU
TO THE ESCALATOR!

07:04.291 --> 07:06.594
[SCOOBY AND SHAGGY
WHIMPERING]

07:16.069 --> 07:17.070
HELLO AGAIN.

07:17.137 --> 07:18.539
LIKE, HI.

07:18.606 --> 07:21.208
WE--WE KIND OF EXPECTED
THIS PLACE TO BE CLOSED.

07:21.274 --> 07:22.610
THEN WHY
ARE YOU HERE?

07:22.676 --> 07:24.578
BECAUSE OF THE ATTACKS
ON HAROLD LING.

07:24.645 --> 07:26.346
WE'RE CHECKING
ON HIS STORE.

07:26.413 --> 07:27.881
HAROLD LING
IS MY FATHER.

07:27.948 --> 07:29.082
I'M MEI LING.

07:29.149 --> 07:31.384
SO THAT EXPLAINS HOW
YOU WERE AT HIS COMPANY

07:31.451 --> 07:33.521
TO SAVE
SHAGGY AND SCOOBY.

07:33.587 --> 07:35.222
IT WAS
MY PLEASURE.

07:35.288 --> 07:36.657
[BONK]
OOPS!

07:36.724 --> 07:39.126
WHY THE GLITTERY MASKS
AND OUTFITS?

07:39.192 --> 07:41.428
WE PERFORM FOR
THE NEW YEAR'S FESTIVITIES.

07:41.495 --> 07:44.431
THIS IS MY TEAM
AND MY PARTNER WU.

07:44.498 --> 07:46.734
[LAUGHS]
WU DOESN'T SAY MUCH,

07:46.800 --> 07:49.202
BUT HE'S THE BEST
TEAM LEADER IN CHINA.

07:49.269 --> 07:52.773
OH, PLEASE DON'T
LET MY FATHER KNOW
WE'RE PRACTICING HERE.

07:52.840 --> 07:53.674
WHY NOT?

07:53.741 --> 07:55.475
MY DREAM
WAS TO TRAVEL

07:55.543 --> 07:57.010
WITH THE ACROBATS
ALL OVER THE WORLD,

07:57.077 --> 07:59.713
BUT MY FATHER INSISTED
I STAY HERE

07:59.780 --> 08:01.114
AND TAKE CARE
OF HIS STORE.

08:01.181 --> 08:02.382
THINGS HAVE GONE BADLY

08:02.449 --> 08:04.785
SINCE LOUIE, HIS TOY MAKER,
WAS FIRED.

08:04.852 --> 08:08.088
DO YOU THINK HE'D WANT
TO PAY YOUR FATHER
BACK FOR THAT?

08:08.155 --> 08:09.122
I HOPE NOT.

08:09.189 --> 08:10.524
I HOPE NOT, TOO.

08:10.591 --> 08:13.260
THAT'S WHO MADE MY OLD
BATHTUB PAL DUCK GUY.

08:13.326 --> 08:14.795
WHAT A COINCIDENCE.

08:14.862 --> 08:19.066
LOOK, MY BATHTUB PAL,
DUCK GIRL.

08:19.132 --> 08:20.100
[QUACK]

08:20.167 --> 08:21.268
LIKE,
WHO WOULD THINK?

08:21.334 --> 08:23.203
THOUSANDS OF MILES APART.

08:23.270 --> 08:24.872
Fred: AHEM.

08:24.938 --> 08:26.707
DO YOU KNOW WHERE
WE'D FIND THIS LOUIE?

08:26.774 --> 08:29.342
HIS WORKSHOP
IS SOMEWHERE IN
THE WAREHOUSE DISTRICT.

08:29.409 --> 08:31.244
W.H. 12.

08:31.311 --> 08:32.613
HMM.

08:32.680 --> 08:34.447
THAT COULD BE
WAREHOUSE 12.

08:34.514 --> 08:35.883
THERE'S A DRAGON
ON THE LOOSE.

08:35.949 --> 08:37.651
IT MIGHT BE DANGEROUS
TO STAY HERE.

08:37.718 --> 08:39.620
[LAUGHS]
I'M NOT WORRIED.

08:39.687 --> 08:41.388
BYE, SHAGGY.

08:41.454 --> 08:44.524
[LAUGHS]
LIKE, BYE.

08:45.292 --> 08:47.561
[SHIP'S HORN BLOWS]

08:48.929 --> 08:52.065
MEI LING'S
FATHER FIZZLED
HER ACROBATIC DREAM.

08:52.132 --> 08:54.568
DO YOU THINK SHE'D WANT
TO HURT HIS BUSINESS?

08:54.635 --> 08:57.170
NO WAY.
SHE SEEMS SO NICE.

08:57.237 --> 08:58.505
AND SHE SAVED ME.

08:58.572 --> 08:59.707
ME, TOO.

08:59.773 --> 09:01.208
Velma: HERE'S NUMBER 12.

09:01.274 --> 09:03.110
I HOPE MY HUNCH WAS RIGHT.

09:04.878 --> 09:06.113
HELLO?

09:06.179 --> 09:07.347
ANYBODY HERE?

09:07.414 --> 09:08.816
LET'S BE
VERY CAREFUL

09:08.882 --> 09:10.483
AND NOT TOUCH
ANYTHING.

09:10.550 --> 09:11.985
HEY, CHECK THIS OUT.

09:12.052 --> 09:13.220
SHAGGY, DON'T!

09:13.286 --> 09:14.487
Man: HELP, MEDDLING KIDS.

09:14.554 --> 09:16.790
THEY'RE ON MY TRAIL.
HAD TO FLEE.

09:16.857 --> 09:18.826
MEET ME AT KING'S ROAD
AND WATERFRONT.

09:18.892 --> 09:20.427
LOOK FOR STRIPES.

09:20.493 --> 09:22.495
OH, AND DON'T STEP
IN ANY LOOPS.

09:22.562 --> 09:23.897
WHAT DID HE MEAN
BY LOOPS?

09:23.964 --> 09:26.266
All: WHOA!

09:28.936 --> 09:31.672
AH-HAH!
CAUGHT YOU NOW!

09:32.773 --> 09:35.142
OH. I THOUGHT I
HEARD THAT DRAGON.

09:35.208 --> 09:36.476
WELL, YOU DON'T.

09:36.543 --> 09:39.446
I KNOW I'M CLOSE.
I'M ON ITS TRAIL.

09:39.512 --> 09:41.448
WHAT ARE YOU KIDS
DOING HERE?

09:41.514 --> 09:45.018
Velma: AT THE MOMENT,
LISTENING TO BLOOD
RUSHING TO OUR HEADS.

09:45.085 --> 09:47.054
WELL, I'M WARNING YOU--
STAY OUT OF MY WAY.

09:47.120 --> 09:48.388
WE'LL SURE TRY.

09:48.455 --> 09:51.524
THEY LAUGHED WHEN I
WENT AFTER THE GLOWING
ENERGY BEAST

09:51.591 --> 09:53.727
AND THE PROTOPLASMIC
PLASMA PHANTOM.

09:53.794 --> 09:55.996
Daphne: SOUNDS LIKE WE
TRAVEL IN SIMILAR CIRCLES.

09:56.063 --> 09:59.366
BUT WHO'S GOING TO BE
LAUGHING NOW? ME. HA!

09:59.432 --> 10:02.670
UH, DETECTIVE KANG, AREN'T
YOU FORGETTING SOMETHING?

10:02.736 --> 10:05.939
OH. RIGHT.

10:06.006 --> 10:09.142
Fred: I'VE GOT TO REMEMBER
THIS FOR A FUTURE TRAP.

10:15.182 --> 10:19.319
IF THIS IS KING'S ROAD,
I'D HATE TO SEE
BO'S BOULEVARD.

10:19.386 --> 10:20.553
All: AAH!

10:20.620 --> 10:22.622
Shaggy:
YIKES! STRIPES!

10:25.125 --> 10:26.994
PLEASE, FORGIVE
THE DISGUISES.

10:27.060 --> 10:29.562
I MAKE THEM MYSELF
SO NO ONE WILL
RECOGNIZE ME.

10:29.629 --> 10:31.064
I STILL DON'T
RECOGNIZE YOU.

10:31.131 --> 10:34.234
OH. I'M LOUIE HONG FA,
THE TOY INVENTOR.

10:34.301 --> 10:36.136
THE CREATOR
OF DUCK GUY?

10:36.203 --> 10:39.072
MAN, YOU'RE MY HERO!

10:39.139 --> 10:39.940
LOOK!

10:40.007 --> 10:41.942
I KNOW. I'VE BEEN
FOLLOWING YOU.

10:42.009 --> 10:44.077
I NEED HELP.
MR. LING HAS BLAMED ME

10:44.144 --> 10:46.579
FOR HIS RING ROBBERY
AND THE DRAGON ATTACKS.

10:46.646 --> 10:48.615
HE THINKS YOU MIGHT
BE OUT FOR REVENGE.

10:48.682 --> 10:49.883
BUT I'M NOT.

10:49.950 --> 10:51.819
THERE'S A REAL LIVE
DRAGON AT LARGE.

10:51.885 --> 10:54.387
YOU'VE GOT
TO BELIEVE ME.
NOBODY ELSE WILL.

10:54.454 --> 10:56.223
YOU BROUGHT THE WORLD
DUCK GUY.

10:56.289 --> 10:57.424
I BELIEVE YOU.

10:57.490 --> 10:58.892
ME, TOO.

10:58.959 --> 11:01.862
I NEED SOMEBODY
TO HELP PROVE
I'M INNOCENT.

11:01.929 --> 11:05.198
IF YOU TRY, I'LL
MAKE YOUR DUCK GUY
AS GOOD AS NEW.

11:05.265 --> 11:07.467
COULD YOU GET HIM
TO SAY "QUACK" AGAIN?

11:07.534 --> 11:10.270
IN 7 LANGUAGES.
MR. LING HIMSELF

11:10.337 --> 11:12.873
MIGHT HAVE SOMETHING
TO DO WITH
THE DRAGON ATTACKS.

11:12.940 --> 11:15.075
BUT THEY'VE ALL BEEN
ON HIS OWN PROPERTIES.

11:15.142 --> 11:18.245
I'LL BET THE SAMPAN BOAT
HE LIVES ON HASN'T
BEEN TOUCHED.

11:18.311 --> 11:19.646
IT'S WORTH FINDING OUT.

11:19.713 --> 11:21.782
WE'LL SPLIT UP.
SHAGGY AND SCOOBY,

11:21.849 --> 11:23.751
YOU TAKE DUCK GUY
BACK FOR REPAIRS.

11:23.817 --> 11:24.918
WE'LL MEET YOU
AT THE WAREHOUSE.

11:24.985 --> 11:26.519
HEAR THAT, DUCK GUY?

11:26.586 --> 11:28.856
PRETTY SOON IT'LL BE
YOU AND ME IN THE
BATHTUB AGAIN

11:28.922 --> 11:30.858
PLAYING MARCO POLO!

11:32.092 --> 11:33.761
Daphne: ACCORDING
TO THE DOCK MASTER,

11:33.827 --> 11:36.429
THIS IS
MR. LING'S BOAT.

11:36.496 --> 11:38.999
MR. LING,
ARE YOU HOME?

11:41.034 --> 11:45.305
I THOUGHT MR. LING DIDN'T
KNOW WHAT TO DO WITH THOSE
GIGANTIC MUTANT TOYS.

11:45.372 --> 11:49.209
HE'S GOT A WEB SITE
SELLING GIGANTIC
MUTANT TOYS!

11:49.276 --> 11:52.746
HMM. IF HE'S PLANNING
TO SELL HUGE TOYS,

11:52.813 --> 11:56.149
A HUGE DRAGON
WOULD SURE GET
PEOPLE'S ATTENTION.

12:01.154 --> 12:03.791
RRAAHHRR!

12:07.795 --> 12:09.763
I'LL GET MY DUCK DRILL.

12:09.830 --> 12:11.965
WE'LL HAVE HIM UP
AND WADDLING IN NO TIME.

12:12.032 --> 12:15.135
I HOPE SO. I CAN'T
TAKE A BATH
WITHOUT DUCK GUY.

12:15.202 --> 12:17.604
AND WE'RE ALL STAYING
IN ONE ROOM.

12:17.670 --> 12:18.705
[SNIFFS]

12:18.772 --> 12:20.307
PEE-UUU!

12:23.410 --> 12:26.246
THIS SPOOKY PLACE
JUST SEEMED
TO GET SPOOKIER.

12:26.313 --> 12:28.816
REAH, SPOOKY.

12:32.385 --> 12:33.753
Shaggy: YIKES!

12:39.392 --> 12:41.694
SHAGGY! SCOOBY!

12:41.761 --> 12:43.763
THEY SHOULD BE HERE
BY NOW.

12:43.831 --> 12:46.133
SOMETHING DOESN'T
SEEM RIGHT.

12:47.734 --> 12:49.569
INCLUDING
THIS GOLD STUFF.

12:49.636 --> 12:53.340
[DRAGON ROARING]

13:00.513 --> 13:02.415
RRAAHHRR!

13:02.482 --> 13:05.318
YAAA-WHOA!

13:06.353 --> 13:07.387
UNH!

13:08.488 --> 13:09.923
RRAAHHRR!

13:09.990 --> 13:11.458
RUN FOR THAT ALLEY!

13:18.631 --> 13:21.768
[ROARING]

13:21.835 --> 13:23.070
THAT STOPPED IT.

13:23.136 --> 13:25.172
WE'VE GOT TO FIND
SHAGGY AND SCOOBY.

13:25.238 --> 13:27.707
THIS WAS ON THE FLOOR--
GOLD GLITTER.

13:27.774 --> 13:30.243
I THINK I KNOW WHERE
THEY MIGHT BE.

13:33.646 --> 13:34.747
HUH?

13:34.814 --> 13:37.150
Daphne: SHAGGY,
SCOOBY, ARE YOU OK?

13:37.217 --> 13:40.854
WE WILL BE IF WE
CAN JUST GET TO
THOSE KUMQUATS!

13:41.821 --> 13:43.023
SEEMS LIKE
THE KIDNAPPING

13:43.090 --> 13:45.125
MIGHT HAVE SOMETHING
TO DO WITH MEI LING.

13:45.192 --> 13:47.127
WHY WOULD SHE WANT
US OUT OF THE WAY?

13:47.194 --> 13:48.862
COULD BE SO SHE'S FREE
TO GO WITH HER TEAM

13:48.929 --> 13:51.498
WHEN HER FATHER'S
BUSINESSES ARE
OUT OF BUSINESS.

13:51.564 --> 13:53.000
BUT THIS ONE'S OK.

13:53.066 --> 13:55.102
[DRAGON ROARING]

13:56.703 --> 13:58.972
R-R-R-RUN!

14:06.980 --> 14:08.615
[ROARING]

14:10.517 --> 14:11.618
WHOA!

14:14.287 --> 14:16.356
All: YEE-AAHH!

14:18.425 --> 14:20.360
RRAAHHRR!

14:20.427 --> 14:22.862
All: AAHH!

14:24.797 --> 14:26.133
All: WHOA-AAH!

14:27.234 --> 14:30.237
All: AAHH!

14:46.353 --> 14:49.256
MEI LING.
SHE SAVED US AGAIN.

14:49.322 --> 14:53.426
THE DRAGON ALWAYS
SEEMS TO GO AWAY
BEFORE SHE SHOWS UP.

14:53.493 --> 14:54.894
WHERE? WHERE IS IT?

14:54.962 --> 14:56.263
SHOW ME THE DRAGON!

14:56.329 --> 14:57.530
IT'S GONE NOW.

14:57.597 --> 14:58.698
BUT NOT FOR LONG.

14:58.765 --> 15:00.300
THAT DRAGON'S GOING
TO TAKE A FALL.

15:00.367 --> 15:02.002
THERE WON'T BE
ANY LAUGHS AT ALL

15:02.069 --> 15:05.072
WHEN IT'S HANGING
ON MY WALL!

15:06.639 --> 15:09.509
I'M BEGINNING TO GET
WHY THEY WERE LAUGHING.

15:09.576 --> 15:11.578
HE SURE GOT HERE
QUICKLY.

15:11.644 --> 15:12.579
[ROARS]

15:12.645 --> 15:14.147
HELP!

15:14.214 --> 15:15.315
AAH!

15:15.382 --> 15:17.951
AAH! HELP!

15:20.720 --> 15:22.289
[ROARS]
RUFF!

15:26.693 --> 15:28.628
[LAUGHS]

15:28.695 --> 15:30.563
[ROARS]

15:30.630 --> 15:33.566
THERE'S SOMETHING
IN SCOOBY'S PAWS.

15:33.633 --> 15:35.302
I DIDN'T KNOW
DRAGONS HAD FUR...

15:35.368 --> 15:37.204
AND THIS FUR
LOOKS FAMILIAR.

15:37.270 --> 15:39.739
MEI LING SAVED US.
WE'VE GOT TO SAVE HER.

15:39.806 --> 15:40.873
BUT HOW?

15:40.940 --> 15:42.209
WELL, THE ONLY
CONNECTION

15:42.275 --> 15:44.211
SEEMS TO BE
THE ATTACKS
ON LING'S COMPANY.

15:44.277 --> 15:45.979
HOW ABOUT SCOOBY AND ME?

15:46.046 --> 15:47.981
EVERYWHERE WE GO,
THAT DRAGON BASHES.

15:48.048 --> 15:49.116
YOU'RE RIGHT.

15:49.182 --> 15:50.583
LING'S BOAT
WASN'T TOUCHED.

15:50.650 --> 15:52.385
BUT THE DRAGON
TRASHED
THE WAREHOUSE

15:52.452 --> 15:54.121
WHERE SHAGGY
AND SCOOBY WERE.

15:54.187 --> 15:55.989
IN FACT,
ALL THE ATTACKS

15:56.056 --> 15:58.458
HAVE BEEN PLACES WHERE
SHAGGY AND SCOOBY WERE.

15:59.092 --> 16:00.227
[GULP]
[GULP]

16:00.293 --> 16:02.195
WE NOT ONLY HAVE
TO SAVE MEI LING,

16:02.262 --> 16:03.830
WE HAVE TO SAVE US!

16:03.896 --> 16:05.898
DON'T WORRY.
I'VE GOT A PLAN.

16:05.965 --> 16:07.967
REMEMBER
THAT RESPECTED
OLD SAYING

16:08.035 --> 16:09.536
"FIGHT DRAGON
WITH DUCK?"

16:09.602 --> 16:10.937
NO.
NO.
NEGATIVE.

16:11.004 --> 16:13.106
YEAH, OK. WELL, JUST
GO WITH ME ON THIS ONE.

16:13.173 --> 16:16.009
THE FIRST THING
WE'LL NEED IS DUCK GUY.

16:16.076 --> 16:17.677
DUCK GUY?!

16:19.946 --> 16:21.514
Shaggy: DUCK GUY?

16:21.581 --> 16:25.185
Fred: DUCK GUY
IS NOW 20 FEET TALL
AND ARMOR PROTECTED.

16:25.252 --> 16:27.620
WEB FEET ARE TREATED
FOR VERTICAL CLIMBS,

16:27.687 --> 16:29.856
HOLLOWED OUT
TO ACCOMMODATE
A TANK-LIKE CABIN.

16:29.922 --> 16:31.891
4-WHEEL DRIVE
CUP HOLDER,

16:31.958 --> 16:35.462
AND HIS BILL IS ABLE
TO SHOOT POWERFUL
FIREHOSE STREAMS.

16:35.528 --> 16:36.763
BUT CAN HE FLOAT?

16:36.829 --> 16:38.965
UH...LIKE A DUCK.

16:39.032 --> 16:42.902
AND NOW FOR
PLAN "A", PART 2.

16:42.969 --> 16:45.405
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

16:53.146 --> 16:55.148
WE'VE BEEN LIVE BAIT
BEFORE, SCOOB,

16:55.215 --> 16:59.786
BUT IT TAKES A HECK
OF A LOT OF SCOOBY SNAX
TO BE DRAGON-LIVE BAIT.

16:59.852 --> 17:03.090
REAH.
SURE DOES.

17:04.691 --> 17:05.925
[ROARS]

17:05.992 --> 17:08.228
[YELLING AND SCREAMING]

17:12.965 --> 17:15.302
[HONG KONG HOLIDAY PLAYING]

17:22.409 --> 17:24.711
* FOUND MYSELF IN A PLACE
SO FAR AWAY *

17:24.777 --> 17:27.180
* RISING SUN THAT GOES
WHERE DRAGONS PLAY *

17:27.247 --> 17:31.718
* JASMINE TEA FOR ME
OLD AND NEW *

17:31.784 --> 17:34.487
* FIRECRACKERS, STREETS
DRAGGING ME *

17:34.554 --> 17:36.623
* WAKE ME FROM MYSELF,
I GOTTA DREAM *

17:36.689 --> 17:40.860
* DREAMS SO SWEET LIKE
MIDNIGHT MOON IS BLUE *

17:40.927 --> 17:41.928
* HA HA HA *

17:41.994 --> 17:46.399
* HONG KONG HOLIDAY *

17:46.466 --> 17:51.171
* HONG KONG HOLIDAY *

17:51.238 --> 17:53.606
* TAKE A CASE OF SWEETS,
HURRY BY *

17:53.673 --> 17:55.908
* ELECTRIC BLACK AND BLUE,
SUNNY SKY *

17:55.975 --> 18:00.747
* PULL ME BACK AND FORTH,
STREET KUNG FU *

18:00.813 --> 18:03.350
* BLIND AND SILENT,
HEADFUL OF LULLABIES *

18:03.416 --> 18:05.718
* STREAKS YOU LIKE A
NEW YEAR'S DRAGONFLY *

18:05.785 --> 18:09.689
* HONG KONG RAIN POURS
DOWN GREAT AND TRUE *

18:09.756 --> 18:10.757
* HA HA HA *

18:10.823 --> 18:15.328
* HONG KONG HOLIDAY *

18:15.395 --> 18:20.567
* HONG KONG HOLIDAY *

18:38.385 --> 18:39.386
* HA HA HA *

18:39.452 --> 18:44.056
* HONG KONG HOLIDAY *

18:44.123 --> 18:49.629
* HONG KONG HOLIDAY *

18:49.696 --> 18:51.298
[SONG ENDS]

18:56.102 --> 18:59.038
TIME TO UN-DRAGON
THIS DRAGON.

18:59.105 --> 19:01.541
All: WU?!

19:01.608 --> 19:03.343
LOOK!

19:04.544 --> 19:05.778
WU-HOO!

19:05.845 --> 19:09.816
SHAGGY, THINK BACK
TO THE LAST PARADE.

19:09.882 --> 19:11.918
[SHIVERING]

19:20.293 --> 19:22.995
HE STOLE
THE LING MING RING!

19:23.062 --> 19:24.931
Velma: AND HE HAD HELP.

19:24.997 --> 19:26.233
[FABRIC TEARING]

19:26.299 --> 19:27.700
All: THE ACROBATS!

19:27.767 --> 19:30.136
AND I'LL BET THEY'RE
NOT IN THERE ALONE.

19:30.203 --> 19:31.371
[FABRIC TEARING]

19:31.438 --> 19:32.672
Shaggy: MEI LING!

19:32.739 --> 19:34.073
ARE YOU OK?

19:34.140 --> 19:36.309
THEY STUCK ME HERE
SO I'D STOP SAVING YOU.

19:36.376 --> 19:38.144
WU THOUGH SHAGGY
COULD I.D. HIM,

19:38.211 --> 19:40.513
SO HE USED THE DRAGON
TO SCARE HIM AWAY.

19:40.580 --> 19:42.081
WATCH OUT!

19:42.148 --> 19:43.316
NOT SO FAST!

19:43.383 --> 19:45.151
I'M LEARNING JU-JITSU.

19:45.218 --> 19:46.886
HYAH!

19:46.953 --> 19:48.888
HYAH--WHOO!

19:48.955 --> 19:51.258
[ALL LAUGH]

19:51.324 --> 19:53.025
HYAH--WHOA!

19:53.092 --> 19:54.394
All:UHH!

19:54.461 --> 19:57.597
I KNEW THAT BOOK
WOULD PROTECT US.

19:57.664 --> 19:59.332
Shaggy: SO YOU KIDNAPPED
ME AND SCOOB

19:59.399 --> 20:01.133
TO TAKE US OUT
OF THE DRAGON'S WAY?

20:01.200 --> 20:03.135
YOU KEPT GETTING
INTO TROUBLE.

20:03.202 --> 20:04.704
I DIDN'T WANT YOU HURT.

20:04.771 --> 20:07.674
LIKE THAT'S ANOTHER
THING WE HAVE IN COMMON.

20:07.740 --> 20:09.476
WHAT ABOUT DUCK GUY?

20:09.542 --> 20:11.578
BATH TIME WILL
NEVER BE THE SAME.

20:11.644 --> 20:15.214
SHAGGY, PLEASE TAKE
DUCK GIRL.

20:15.282 --> 20:17.984
I KNOW WE'LL SEE
EACH OTHER AGAIN SOMEDAY.

20:18.050 --> 20:19.051
QUACK.

20:19.118 --> 20:20.320
[LAUGHS]

20:20.387 --> 20:21.588
LIKE I THINK THIS
IS THE BEGINNING

20:21.654 --> 20:23.122
OF A BEAUTIFUL
FRIENDSHIP.

20:23.189 --> 20:24.156
QUACK!

20:24.223 --> 20:26.593
FOR DUCK GUY, TOO.

20:29.161 --> 20:31.398
[STEAM WHISTLE BLOWS]

20:32.632 --> 20:33.833
NOT SO FAST!

20:33.900 --> 20:37.404
HE'S STILL WEARING
THE LING MING
CANDY RING.

20:40.273 --> 20:41.408
SCOOBY--

20:41.474 --> 20:43.175
[GULPS, BELCHES]

20:43.242 --> 20:45.244
DOO.
